nload PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534100\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534100\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yhg1665702777428.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yhg1665702777428.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yhg1665702777428.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yhg1665702777428\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      SQL Support on MySQL\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__sql_support_on_mysql_161673\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Both the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript command and SQL Editor are supported.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__p_d54170e1_d54171e1_d54172e1\">Tthe MySQL connector fully supports the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript command. You can perform almost any task with MySQL SQL Editor that you can accomplish using ProcScript.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__topic_d35817e1_d35818e1_d35819e1_d35820e1_d35821e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d658202e62\">\n                        \n Allowed Commands\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__p_d54176e1_d54177e1_d54178e1\">For a complete list of SQL commands which cannot be executed within a user transaction, see your MySQL documentation. The network protocol you use can influence the type of commands that you are allowed to issue.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__topic_d35822e1_d35823e1_d35824e1_d35825e1_d35826e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d658202e71\">\n                        \n Transaction Control\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__p_d54182e1_d54183e1_d54184e1\">The MQL connector does not change transaction state before entering and before leaving the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript statement.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__p_d54185e1_d54186e1_d54187e1\">Transaction processing should be avoided in SQL Editor and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript, because the connector cannot manage a transaction which it did not initiate. The commands which involve transaction management are as follows:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__li_d25106e1_d25107e1_d25108e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> (ProcScript command)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__li_d25109e1_d25110e1_d25111e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> (ProcScript command)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__li_d25112e1_d25113e1_d25114e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">commit transaction</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__li_d25115e1_d25116e1_d25117e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">rollback transaction</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__li_d25118e1_d25119e1_d25120e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">begin transaction</code>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you perform transaction management, once the transaction finishes, you must ensure that the logon path is returned to the same state that it was in before the transaction management was performed. If you do not do this, the MQL connector does not understand the correct state of the connection.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__topic_d35827e1_d35828e1_d35829e1_d35830e1_d35831e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d658202e125\">\n                        \n Monitoring SQL in the Message Frame\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__p_d54191e1_d54192e1_d54193e1\">If requested in the application shell, the SQL generated by Uniface can be sent to the message frame. User-defined messages from stored procedures also appear here. Error messages from MySQL are always sent to the message frame.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__p_d54194e1_d54195e1_d54196e1\">To receive all MySQL information messages, results, and user-defined messages from stored procedures in the message frame, set the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pri</span> command line switch to 32 or higher.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__topic_d35832e1_d35833e1_d35834e1_d35835e1_d35836e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d658202e141\">\n                        \n Determining Defined Keys\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yhg1665702777428__p_d54200e1_d54201e1_d54202e1\">Refer to the MySQL documentation.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534100\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534100\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SQL Support on MySQL Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SQL Support on MySQL Both the sql ProcScript command and SQL Editor are supported. Tthe MySQL connector fully supports the sql ProcScript command. You can perform almost any task with MySQL SQL Editor that you can accomplish using ProcScript. Allowed Commands For a complete list of SQL commands which cannot be executed within a user transaction, see your MySQL documentation. The network protocol you use can influence the type of commands that you are allowed to issue. Transaction Control The MQL connector does not change transaction state before entering and before leaving the sql ProcScript statement. Transaction processing should be avoided in SQL Editor and sql ProcScript, because the connector cannot manage a transaction which it did not initiate. The commands which involve transaction management are as follows: commit (ProcScript command) rollback (ProcScript command) commit transaction rollback transaction begin transaction Note: If you perform transaction management, once the transaction finishes, you must ensure that the logon path is returned to the same state that it was in before the transaction management was performed. If you do not do this, the MQL connector does not understand the correct state of the connection. Monitoring SQL in the Message Frame If requested in the application shell, the SQL generated by Uniface can be sent to the message frame. User-defined messages from stored procedures also appear here. Error messages from MySQL are always sent to the message frame. To receive all MySQL information messages, results, and user-defined messages from stored procedures in the message frame, set the /pri command line switch to 32 or higher. Determining Defined Keys Refer to the MySQL documentation. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}